1. switch to SonarQube namespace
		Ø kubectl config set-context --current --namespace=sonarqube

2. Create Storage Class , PV and PVC for jenkins
   	Ø Refert to SC-Jenkins, PV-Jenkins, PVC-Jenkins yaml files in the same directory
	
3. Create sonarqube-values.yaml
    Ø Refert to values yaml files in the same directory

4. Install SonarQube Developer Edition using helm
		Ø helm repo add sonarqube https://SonarSource.github.io/helm-chart-sonarqube
		Ø helm repo update
		Ø helm install sonarqube sonarqube/sonarqube -f sonarqube-values.yaml --namespace sonarqube

5. Expose the Nexus service to access
		Ø kubectl port-forward service/sonarqube-sonarqube 9000:9000 --namespace sonarqube

Troubleshooting Tips:
    # Make sure that you give a right permission to the local volume files
      Ø sudo chmod 777 -R /tmp/sonarqube
